    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Unless grpc-ruby exposes the package's API explicitly somehow, I don't believe transitive dependencies are part of any defined behavior, and that removing or altering them shouldn't be considered a breaking change. We've had similar policies in the past with Python. CC @nathanielmanistaatgoogle to confirm.\r\n\r\nIf you need a package, you should explicitly depend on it."
